name: Cosmo Can
text: Always pretty quick, a good pizza and decent beer picks. Salad bar limited. Totally family friendly. Bring quarters if you have anyone under 12. Who doesn't love random temp tattoos and small plastic bubble characters to step on later?!

name: Sabrina Blackstone
text: Their pizza is good but prices are outrageous... the cashier girl even got annoyed at me for running to my car for a $2 off coupon so my medium pizza would be under 20 bucks. I guess she didn't like being torn away from her boyfriends lap …More

name: Jacob Smith
text: Management is not that nice.. And half off Tuesdays? Only if you purchase certain pizzas. So that means no gluten free pizza (which they can't guarantee it's even gluten free when you order it GLUTEN FREE) and oh... No personal pizzas. …More

name: Steven A Martin Sr.
text: Yolanda and her cousin Cameron are great people. Always very helpful and the food is always good. I recommend this straw hat to everyone.

text: Amazing food, prices, and the customer service is over the top!

name: Jason Lynn
text: Ready to taste card board with cheese and canned tomatoes? You found your place. Save your money and buy cat food.

text: Great old school neighborhood pizzeria with plenty of TVs and local feel -- pizza is very good, sauce has a mild spicy kick to it, overall tastes like a mix between Mountain Mike's and Roundtable.

name: Susan Wise

text: Their online prices aren't up to date I placed an order expecting it to be $17 as it says online. then they said it would be $25. The top notch employee then says it's impossible their website says that, and that I don't know what I'm talking about while I'm staring at the screen. The employees are ignorant and unprofessional
